'''Arne Løchen''' (20 November 1850 – 22 August 1930) was a Norwegian psychologist, philosopher and literary researcher. [[File:ArneLøchen.jpg|thumb|Arne Løchen]] Arne Løchen was born in [[Vang, Hedmark|Vang]] (now [[Hamar]]), in [[Hedmark]] county, [[Norway]]. He was the twin brother of [[Einar Løchen]], politician for the [[Liberal Party (Norway)|Liberal Party]]. His family also included his brothers, [[Kalle Løchen]] (1865-1893) who was an artist and [[Hjalmar Løken]], editor of the ''[[Dagsposten]]'' and ''[[Norske Intelligenz-Seddeler]]''.
Løchen was awarded [[Examen philosophicum|ex. phil.]] (1870) and doctorate (1886). He was a professor of philosophy at the [[University of Oslo]] (1900-1921). Among his works is an essay on [[Henrik Ibsen|Ibsen]] regarded as important for later research,<ref name=nt-1882-loechen>{{cite magazine |title=Om den udvikling, Ibsens moralske grundandskuelse har gjennemgaaet |first=Arne |last=Løchen | year=1882 |pages=412-444 |magazine=[[Nyt Tidsskrift]] |volume=1|language=Norwegian |editor=[[Ernst Sars|Sars, J. E.]] |editor2=[[Olaf Skavlan|Skavlan, Olaf]] |location=Kristiania }}</ref><ref name=snl>{{cite encyclopedia |title=Arne Løchen |first=Knut Eirik |last=Tranøy |encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]] |publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget |location=Oslo |url=http://www.snl.no/Arne_Løchen |language=Norwegian | accessdate=22 June 2010 }}</ref> and a monography on [[Johan Sebastian Welhaven]]. He was co-editor of the magazine ''[[Nyt Tidsskrift]]'' from 1892 to 1895. He was a member of the [[Norwegian Academy of Science]] from 1898. He was decorated a Knight of the [[Order of the Dannebrog]] in 1916.<ref name=nbl>{{cite encyclopedia |title=Arne Løchen |encyclopedia=[[Norsk biografisk leksikon]]|first=Thor Inge |last=Rørvik |editor=[[Knut Helle|Helle, Knut]] |publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget |location=Oslo|url=http://www.snl.no/.nbl_biografi/Arne_Løchen/utdypning |language=Norwegian|accessdate=22 June 2010}}</ref>
==Selected works== * ''Om J. Stuart Mills Logik. En kritisk studie'', 1885 * ''Spørgsmaal vedkommende de afasiske Sygdomme'', 1888 * ''J. S. Welhaven. Liv og skrifter'', 1898–1900 * ''Digtning og videnskab'', 1913 * ''Fantasien. Et stykke av sjælelæren'', 1917
