'''Josephine Acosta Pasricha''' (born March 26, 1945) is a [[Philippines|Filipino]] [[indologist]] who translated the "Ramacharitamanasa" of Tulasi Dasa, the [[Hindi]] translation of the [[Ramayana]] by Valmiki in [[Sanskrit]], into the [[Filipino language]].

Pasricha herself was mentored by Filipino indologist [[Juan R. Francisco]]. She made a complete unpublished [[Filipino language|Filipino]] translation of the seven books of the "Ramacharitamanasa" of Tulasi Dasa, accompanied with contextual, intertextual and textual analysis, and cross-references with [[Sanskrit]], [[Hindi]] and [[English language|English]] translations.

An expert in the [[Ramayana]] and the [[Mahabharata]], she is also a [[Ford Foundation]] research scholar to the [[University of Delhi]]. She is currently teaching [[humanities]] in the [[University of Santo Tomas]] in [[Manila]]. In the undergraduate level, she teaches Art Appreciation, [[Aesthetics]] and Hermeneutics. In the graduate level, she teaches Advanced Aesthetics, Advanced Hermeneutics, Cultural Studies, Feminist Philosophy and Theology of the Body.

She is one of the editors of the [[Filipino language|Filipino]] translation of [[Kama Sutra]] by Marvin Reyes and Paz Panganiban. The translation is based on the work of [[Vatsyayana]] and [[Sir Richard Burton]].

==Personal life==
Pasricha is married to an Indian man and has two daughters,<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.philstar.com/lifestyle/health-and-family/2006/07/18/348025/letter-mother-daughter-her-graduation|title=Letter of a mother to a daughter on her graduation|date=18 July 2006|first=Josephine Acosta|last=Pasricha|website=Philstar.com|accessdate=28 November 2018}}</ref> Sarina and Satya (also known as Selene). Both daughters were raised in the Philippines and now work in India for a global Indian Informational Technology company.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.philstar.com/lifestyle/health-and-family/2005/12/13/311996/her-name-small | title=Her name is Small|date=13 December 2005|first=Josephine Acosta|last=Pasricha|website=Philstar.com|accessdate=28 November 2018}}</ref>

