==Release and reception== [[File:Dr. Nader Kadhim.jpg|thumb|upright|left|[[Nader Kadhim]] signing a copy of the book in the 2014 Bahrain Book Fair]]
''Saving Hope'' was published by Masaa Publishing & Distribution in Bahrain and Kuwait in 2013, with the subtitle, ''The Long Way to the Arab Spring''.<ref name="W 13.4.2012"/> Unlike Kadhim's three previous books, which were published gradually as articles in the media, no parts of ''Saving Hope'' were published before the official release.<ref name="W 22.6.2013"/> The cover of the 314 pages book showed a Tunisian woman waving the [[V sign]].<ref name="Ayam 1.6.2013"/> The book has received favorable reviews in various media outlets.
Writing for [[Al-Wasat (Bahraini newspaper)|''Al-Wasat'']], Mohammed Jalal praised the book's title and subtitle saying they reflected positiveness and reality.<ref>{{cite news|script-title=ar:ملاحظات عابرة على هامش كتاب "إنقاذ الأمل" لنادر كاظم (1)|author=Mohammed Nuaman Jalal|work=Al-Wasat|date=4 January 2014|url=http://www.alwasatnews.com/4137/news/read/844095/1.html|accessdate=9 April 2014|language=Arabic|trans-title=Passing notes on the margins of Nader Kadhim's ''Saving Hope'' (1)}}</ref> He also stated that ''Saving Hope'' was Kadhim's most important book so far.<ref>{{cite news|script-title=ar:ملاحظات عابرة على هامش كتاب "إنقاذ الأمل" لنادر كاظم (2)|author=Mohammed Nuaman Jalal|work=Al-Wasat|date=6 January 2014|url=http://www.alwasatnews.com/4139/news/read/844710/1.html|accessdate=9 April 2014|language=Arabic|trans-title=Passing notes on the margins of Nader Kadhim's ''Saving Hope'' (2)}}</ref> Writing for the same newspaper, Habib Haidar expressed his admire to the large amount of sources Kadhim used and was able to plot in a homogeneous way that is easy to read. He also noted that two thirds of the book were dedicated to the "memory of hope" and only 100 pages discussed the Arab Spring.<ref name="W 22.6.2013"/>
Hassan Madan reviewed the book in 5 articles published in [[Al Ayam (Bahrain)|''Al Ayam'']]. He considered it the first Bahraini attempt to analyze the roots of the Arab Spring. He noted that throughout the book, the author had argued against [[Jean-François Lyotard|Lyotard]]'s proposal by stating that local narratives had reached an impasse. While praising his division of the "memory of hope", Madan thought that Kadhim should have expanded more about the divisions between the first and the second wave and should have explored more about [[Marxist]] parties in the Arab world.<ref>{{cite news|author=Hassan Madan|work=Al Ayam|accessdate=9 April 2014|script-title=ar:قراءة لنادر كاظم|date=22 April 2013|url=http://www.alayam.com/writers/7900|language=Arabic}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author=Hassan Madan|work=Al Ayam|accessdate=9 April 2014|script-title=ar:نادر كاظم: فقدان الأمل أم إنقاذه|date=23 April 2013|url=http://www.alayam.com/writers/7918|language=Arabic}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author=Hassan Madan|work=Al Ayam|accessdate=9 April 2014|script-title=ar:نادر كاظم والموجات الثلاث|date=24 April 2013|url=http://www.alayam.com/writers/7933|language=Arabic}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author=Hassan Madan|work=Al Ayam|accessdate=9 April 2014|script-title=ar:نادر كاظم ونقد المجتمع المدني|date=25 April 2013|url=http://www.alayam.com/writers/7944|language=Arabic}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author=Hassan Madan|work=Al Ayam|accessdate=9 April 2014|script-title=ar:القديم يموت والجديد لا يولد|date=28 April 2013|url=http://www.alayam.com/writers/7978|language=Arabic}}</ref> Writing for the same newspaper, Mahir Abdulqadir praised the thesis of the book, stating that unlike many of the superficial analysis of the Arab Spring, Kadhim succeeded in tackling and examining the Arabic subconscious while keeping the reader in suspense until the last pages. He however criticized the book for not covering the "West aggressive attitude to the [Arab] Renaissance".<ref name="Ayam 1.6.2013">{{cite news|script-title=ar:إنقاذ الأمل.. قراءة فى كتاب نادر كاظم|language=Arabic|url=http://alayam.com/News/sevendays/Visions/157776|author=Mahir Abdulqadir|date=1 June 2013|accessdate=10 April 2014|work=[[Al Ayam (Bahrain)]]}}</ref>
One attendant of a cultural seminar about the book criticized it for lacking Islamic theorizing, while another described it as too optimistic. Overall comments were however positive.<ref>{{cite news|script-title=ar:اشتباكات نقدية وقراءات مختلفة لـ "إنقاذ الأمل"|url=http://www.alayam.com/News/alayam/Culture/163792|date=26 June 2013|accessdate=10 April 2014|work=Al Ayam|language=Arabic}}</ref> Writing for ''Al-Bilad'' newspaper, Mohammed al-Mahfodh stated that the book was well worth reading and stopping by.<ref>{{cite news|script-title=ar:"إنقاذ الأمل" قراءة مختلفة للربيع العربيّ|url=http://www.albiladpress.com/column232-12970.html|date=17 April 2013|accessdate=10 April 2014|work=Al-Bilad|language=Arabic|author=Mohammed al-Mahfodh}}</ref> A review by ''[[Al-Hayat]]'' warned against judging the book from its optimistic cover image or title. It praised the book and described it as a "thoughtful and interesting study".<ref>{{cite news|script-title=ar:"إنقاذ الأمل" ... الصعود إلى الأسفل|language=Arabic|url=http://daharchives.alhayat.com/issue_archive/Hayat%20KSA/2013/8/6/%D8%A7%D9%95%D9%86%D9%82%D8%A7%D8%B0-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%94%D9%85%D9%84-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B5%D8%B9%D9%88%D8%AF-%D8%A7%D9%95%D9%84%D9%89-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%94%D8%B3%D9%81%D9%84.html|work=[[Al-Hayat]]|date=6 August 2013|accessdate=10 April 2014}}</ref> Fahad al-Hindal praised the author's [[critical reading]] of the three waves of hope in a review published in ''[[Al Rai (Kuwaiti newspaper)|Al Rai]]'' newspaper.<ref>{{cite news |script-title=ar:فاصلة / إنقاذ الأمل... صوت العقل |author=Fahad Tawfiq al-Hindal |newspaper=[[Al Rai (Kuwaiti newspaper)|Al Rai]] |url=http://www.alraimedia.com/Articles.aspx?id=443236 |date=1 August 2013 |accessdate=10 April 2014 |language=ar}}</ref>
